## Peer: WorkStation — Active Mission

# Active Mission

_The current live assignment. One objective at a time._
_Replace contents when the objective changes. Do not accumulate history here — that belongs in mission-log.md._

## Objective

Phase 1: Make WorkStation the single, reliable entrypoint for the full platform stack. One command (`./scripts/up.sh`) starts everything and confirms it's healthy before returning.

## Context

`up.sh` previously started docker compose and exited immediately with no health verification. Phase 1 adds: per-component structured logging, SwitchBoard health wait (hard fail if unreachable), optional Plane startup controlled by `PLANE_ENABLED` env var, and `aider` binary check for the local lane (soft warn).

## Definition of Done

- `./scripts/up.sh` starts SwitchBoard, waits for `/health`, and fails hard if it doesn't come up
- Plane is started if `PLANE_ENABLED=true`, skipped otherwise (non-blocking in either case)
- Local lane readiness (aider) is checked and reported, non-blocking
- Per-component `[OK]` / `[WARN]` / `[SKIP]` / `[FAIL]` output
- Running the script twice is safe (docker compose up --detach is idempotent)
- `startup-flow.md` updated to match new behaviour
- `.env.example` documents `PLANE_ENABLED`

